section.programlisting:
@Path("widgets")
public class WidgetsResource {
  @GET
  public Widgets get() {
    return new Widgets();
  }
}

public class Widgets {
  @Ref(resource=WidgetsResource.class)
  URI u;
}

section.para:
The source for URI template parameter values can be changed using the
                @Binding annotation, E.g. the following two annotations are
            equivalent:

            In order to add the Declarative Linking feature register &jersey.media.LinkingFeature;


                Creating JAX-RS application with Declarative Linking feature enabled.

                // Create JAX-RS application.
final Application application = new ResourceConfig()
.packages("org.glassfish.jersey.examples.linking")
.register(LinkingFeature.class);
